1939 and had a series of big budget US films with the character named in the title since 1989.\n}}</ref><ref>{{cite web\n|date= November 13, 2008\n|last= Akbar\n|first= Arifa\n|url= https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/films/news/mayor-of-batman-takes-on-the-might-of-gotham-city-1015835.html\n|title= \nMayor of Batman takes on the might of Gotham City\n|publisher= [[The Independent]]\n|accessdate= November 14, 2008\n|quote= No one from the town of Batman has explained why it has taken so many years to take legal action.\n}}</ref><ref>{{cite web\n |date         = November 12, 2008\n |last         = Modine\n |first        = Austin\n |url          = https://www.theregister.co.uk/2008/11/12/batman_city_sues_batman/\n |title        = Batman sues Batman over Batman\n |publisher    = [[The Register]]\n |accessdate   = November 14, 2008\n |quote        = Of course, one could also speculate the city could have figured this out much sooner with the assistance of Batman, the world's greatest detective.\n |archive-url  = https://web.archive.org/web/20081113235223/http://www.theregister.co.uk/2008/11/12/batman_city_sues_batman/\n |archive-date = 2008-11-13\n |url-status     = live\n}}</ref><ref>{{cite web\n |date         = November 12, 2008\n |last         = Serpe\n |first        = Gina\n |url          = http://www.eonline.com/uberblog/b68391_batmans_latest_archenemy_batman.html\n |title        = Batman's Latest Archenemy: Batman\n |publisher    = [[E! Online]]\n |accessdate   = November 14, 2008\n |quote        = Which begs the question of where hizzoner has been the past 70 years.\n |archive-url  = https://web.archive.org/web/20110522064313/http://www.eonline.com/uberblog/b68391_batmans_latest_archenemy_batman.html\n |archive-date = 2011-05-22\n |url-status     = live\n}}</ref>\n\nIn February 2008 the mayor was sentenced to 10 months imprisonment for promoting terrorism. In 2019 the [[European Court of Human Rights]] sentenced Turkey to pay Kalkan the sum of 3500 [[Euro|Euros]] in compensation.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://m.bianet.org/bianet/politics/213827-ecthr-former-mayor-of-batman-shall-be-paid-compensation|title=ECtHR: Former Mayor of Batman Shall be Paid Compensation|last=|first=|date=|website=Bianet|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=5 March 2020}}</ref>  \n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Kalkan, Huseyin}}\n[[Category:1950 births]]\n[[Category:2010 deaths]]\n[[Category:Mayors of places in Turkey]]\n[[Category:Democratic Society Party politicians]]\n[[Category:Members of the 21st Parliament of Turkey]]\n\n\n{{Turkey-mayor-stub}}\n", "text_old": "[[File:Batman, Turkey.jpg|thumbnail|right|Batman sign]]\n'''H\u00fcseyin Kalkan''' ({{circa|1950}}) was mayor of [[Batman, Turkey|Batman]] in Southeast Anatolia, [[Turkey]], and a member of the [[Democratic Society Party]].  He gained international notoriety November 2008 after he announced plans to sue [[Christopher Nolan]], director of ''[[The Dark Knight (film)|The Dark Knight]]'' film, over the allegedly unauthorized use of his city's name.<ref name=\"CNN\">{{cite web\n |date         = November 13, 2008\n |url          = http://edition.cnn.com/2008/SHOWBIZ/Movies/11/12/batman.turkey.movie/\n |title        = Holy court action! Can 'Dark Knight' beat Turkish mayor?\n |publisher    = [[CNN]]\n |accessdate   = November 13, 2008\n |archive-url  = https://web.archive.org/web/20110522165212/http://edition.cnn.com/2008/SHOWBIZ/Movies/11/12/batman.turkey.movie/\n |archive-date = 2011-05-22\n |url-status     = live\n}}</ref><ref name=\"TELE\">{{cite web\n |date         = November 11, 2008\n |last         = Bailey\n |first        = Charlotte\n |url          = https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/europe/turkey/3437401/Turkish-mayor-suing-Batman-director-for-stealing-his-citys-name.html\n |title        = Turkish mayor suing Batman director for 'stealing his city's name'\n |publisher    = [[The Daily Telegraph]]\n |accessdate   = November 13, 2008